column2: A sunny- warm day after many days of rain.
Weeds from shore to 50 feet out.
10-20 mph winds previous day- weedy shoreline.
We have moved up here permanently this summer.
Public perception due to weeds.  Clear skies.
There was a lot of seed bloom along the east shoreline.  Clear skies- slight breeze.
Water calm- hardly any new weed growth- lots of pollen on water.
Water slightly choppy.  Minimal boat traffic- hot day- 85 degrees F.
Partly cloudy.  Water slightly choppy.  No boat traffic.
Lots of boat traffic.  Sunny.  No wind.  Very hot.  95 degrees F.
No boat traffic.  N wind.  Cool + sunny day.
The lake is relatively quiet for July.
Labor Day- lake starting to turn over.
Ice is forming in the bays.
Mostly Sunny S Wind 5mph. Loon on nest for 1st time seen
Rain during prior evening approx 0.7in. Partly sunny SSW Wind 5-10mph . Able to see banded loons. Male is on nest
2 Loon chicks on lake 3 days old
Partly sunny. Dark clouds to west. 2 loons and 2 loon chicks present. Chicks are 4 weeks old today. Lake weeds are very thick this week.
Several heavy rains over the last 10 days. Water clarity is reduced and looks brown from unusual high amounts of run-off. Lake level is the highest I have ever seen since I first came here 1986
Water level high from 2 inch rain 2 days ago but water quality looks OK
Reading is 7 days after a major rain of 5.5 inches
